lua — Lua interpreter / REPL

SYNOPSIS
  lua                              REPL
  lua FILE [arg...]                run FILE
  lua -e 'chunk' [arg...]          evaluate a chunk

DESCRIPTION
  Without arguments, opens an interactive REPL with multi-line input
  support: a chunk that ends mid-expression triggers a continuation
  prompt. Each line is first compiled as `return EXPR` (so `1+2` prints
  `3`); if that fails it is recompiled as a statement.

  With FILE, loads and runs the script. arg[0] is FILE, arg[1..] are
  the trailing command-line arguments. The script returns either a
  number (used as the exit code) or nothing (exit 0).

  -e evaluates the next argument as Lua source.

  Both modes share a sandbox provided by lib/devtools/repl.lua so
  globals set in one REPL line stay visible in later ones.

EXAMPLES
  lua                                    enter REPL
  lua /home/test.lua a b                 run with arg = {[0]=path, [1]="a", [2]="b"}
  lua -e 'print(_VERSION)'

SEE ALSO
  repl(1)
